						<summary>

						<p>On the gold plated staff.</p>						

						<p>Mīnākshamma.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">(Śaka 1656,) Ānanda, Māgha śu. 2, Tuesday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1735 A.D. January 14, Tuesday f.d.t. °17.</hi></p>						

						<p>States that the staff weighing 1638 <hi rend="italic">vaga (Varāha gadyāṇa)</hi> was the gift of Kṛishṇājamma, when Mīnākshamma, the wife <hi rend="italic">(Paṭṭamahishi)</hi> Vijayaraṅga Chōkkanātha was ruling. Published; <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XXIV, No. 566.</p>						

						</summary>
